  "prompt": "Will Northern Ireland have an independence referendum after the Brexit vote?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the question of an independence referendum for Northern Ireland remains a topic of debate and speculation, particularly in the context of Brexit. The Good Friday Agreement allows for a referendum on Irish unity if it appears likely that a majority of Northern Ireland's population would support it, and the political landscape has shifted since Brexit.\n\nWhile there have been calls from some political parties and groups for a referendum, the UK's government has not granted a clear green light for such a vote. Political opinions on the matter are deeply divided, and many factors, including public sentiment, political leadership, and broader discussions around the union, will influence whether an independence referendum occurs in the near future.\n\nFor the most current and specific developments, it would be advisable to consult recent news sources or political analyses, as circumstances may have evolved since my last update.",
